  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2000-07-27", 
    "text": "Workplace Safety Improvement Act - Amends the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970 (OSHA) to prohibit citing an employer for a violation on a multi-employer work site if the employer has: (1) not created the condition that caused the violation; (2) no employees exposed to the violation; or (3) not assumed responsibility for ensuring compliance by other employers on the work site."
  }, 
